1
00:02:22,173 --> 00:02:24,095
Attention!

2
00:02:29,573 --> 00:02:31,422
Stand at ease!

3
00:02:33,453 --> 00:02:34,787
Major Vijay Malhotra reporting sir.

4
00:02:35,773 --> 00:02:37,250
- Come. Sit down.
- Thank you.

5
00:02:40,173 --> 00:02:41,817
- Yes Vijay?
- Sir.

6
00:02:42,493 --> 00:02:45,365
The truck carrying arms to the border
Met with an accident last month.

7
00:02:46,008 --> 00:02:49,233
And the task to enquire
the fire in the jeep,

8
00:02:49,773 --> 00:02:51,101
I've prepared its' report.

9
00:02:51,142 --> 00:02:55,577
- So what's the outcome?
- It was a plan not an accident.

10
00:02:56,147 --> 00:02:57,969
The aim of being stealing of arms.

11
00:02:58,592 --> 00:03:03,757
Means our people are involved.
Must hand the case to intelligence.

12
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:07,954
I have a request.
The truck that is to leave tomorrow

13
00:03:08,770 --> 00:03:11,522
give me the responsibility of taking
it to the border security force.

14
00:03:12,587 --> 00:03:16,687
If this happens again,
the arms looters will be uncontrollable.

15
00:03:17,122 --> 00:03:17,507
Okay.

16
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,600
Why doesn't this plane fly?

17
00:03:22,727 --> 00:03:26,590
What are you saying, son?
Do toys ever fly?

18
00:03:26,702 --> 00:03:28,675
Buy me a flying plane.

19
00:03:28,877 --> 00:03:31,567
First grow up. Then you'll see

20
00:03:31,607 --> 00:03:36,343
you'll have more planes
than people have cars. Go.

21
00:03:36,627 --> 00:03:40,145
For the time being, make do with this.

22
00:03:41,285 --> 00:03:44,727
If you fill A, B, C...
in his mind instead of this

23
00:03:45,377 --> 00:03:47,359
he'd learn to write his name.

24
00:03:47,907 --> 00:03:51,695
He will learn.
The alphabets are not leaving India.

25
00:03:52,212 --> 00:03:53,656
But look at his age.

26
00:03:54,155 --> 00:03:55,220
He's grown so big.

27
00:03:55,497 --> 00:03:58,159
You neither showed him a
book, nor did he see a school.

28
00:03:58,505 --> 00:03:59,678
Aren't you at all worried?

29
00:03:59,702 --> 00:04:05,319
Buy a couple of buffaloes with
the money you'll spend on books.

30
00:04:05,693 --> 00:04:09,013
The boy will drink milk
and become as tough as us!

31
00:04:09,036 --> 00:04:11,694
He'll become as clever as brother.
You won't believe it.

32
00:04:19,025 --> 00:04:22,775
- What is it?
- Sir has called for an urgent meeting.

33
00:04:23,315 --> 00:04:24,268
What meeting?

34
00:04:24,309 --> 00:04:27,179
Nothing as such but he
has called everybody.

35
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,817
BALDEV: Subhedar Pratap Singh has come.

36
00:04:28,856 --> 00:04:33,208
That's fine but what about the cash
for the arms we gave last time?

37
00:04:33,249 --> 00:04:35,772
He's given this bag full!

38
00:04:38,704 --> 00:04:41,562
- How much is it?
- I can't count much.

39
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:44,660
I'll weigh it if you say.
Must be 7 or 8 kilos with the bag.

40
00:04:44,862 --> 00:04:49,962
No need. You wait at the corner,

41
00:04:50,013 --> 00:04:51,247
- I'll change and come.
- Okay.

42
00:04:59,260 --> 00:05:03,134
Are you doing the duty for which the
government gave you this uniform?

43
00:05:03,313 --> 00:05:05,562
Of course! That's what I'm doing!

44
00:05:05,775 --> 00:05:08,457
You were but no more!

45
00:05:09,305 --> 00:05:11,532
Earlier 3000 rupees used to come
on the first of every month.

46
00:05:12,397 --> 00:05:14,457
Now millions come at any date!

47
00:05:15,483 --> 00:05:18,376
I am asking, why? What do we lack?

48
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:22,549
What an illiterate woman!
I want to live, enjoy!

49
00:05:24,373 --> 00:05:26,125
By selling your country?

50
00:05:26,293 --> 00:05:29,833
Do you want me to spend
all my life carrying a gun?

51
00:05:30,065 --> 00:05:31,991
And die at the enemy's hand someday?

52
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:34,130
You want to be a widow?

53
00:05:34,973 --> 00:05:36,937
That widow is better than a woman

54
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:40,101
whose husband is a martyr for the nation.

55
00:05:41,315 --> 00:05:43,576
I can bare to see you dying by a bullet.

56
00:05:44,773 --> 00:05:47,493
But I can't bare the
stigma of a traitor on you!

57
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,167
- Shanti!
- I am saying it for the last time

58
00:05:50,121 --> 00:05:51,721
don't be loyal to me.

59
00:05:52,573 --> 00:05:57,093
But if you're disloyal to your
country, I won't forgive you!

60
00:05:58,293 --> 00:06:00,842
- Mother!
- Don't try to teach me!

61
00:06:01,335 --> 00:06:03,329
I can leave my wife for money!

62
00:06:12,391 --> 00:06:14,277
Subhedar Pratap Singh has come.

63
00:06:15,394 --> 00:06:19,745
What's the matter?
DK always meets after delivery of arms.

64
00:06:20,502 --> 00:06:23,330
What meeting is this beforehand?

65
00:06:36,627 --> 00:06:39,185
I've called this meeting

66
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:46,917
because the truck of arms which is
going to the border with you tomorrow,

67
00:06:48,478 --> 00:06:51,912
you can't loot it easily.

68
00:06:54,145 --> 00:06:58,647
- Why?
- Because... another in charge is coming.

69
00:07:00,042 --> 00:07:02,173
Major Vijay Malhotra.

70
00:07:03,102 --> 00:07:04,542
How did you find out?

71
00:07:04,793 --> 00:07:09,432
From our fourth partner,
Jaswant Dalal, Major's driver.

72
00:07:09,942 --> 00:07:12,335
He is a very strict officer.

73
00:07:13,173 --> 00:07:17,011
With him around,
forget trucks we can't steal a nail!

74
00:07:17,052 --> 00:07:20,105
Opportunity never strikes again.

75
00:07:21,702 --> 00:07:27,627
The truck carries latest arms worth
10 crores that sell like hot cakes.

76
00:07:28,302 --> 00:07:31,879
Each of us 4 partners can earn 2.5 crores.

77
00:07:32,425 --> 00:07:33,027
2.5 crores?

78
00:07:35,239 --> 00:07:39,050
Let it happened anything,
we will have those weapons.

79
00:07:39,797 --> 00:07:41,957
Best of luck gentlemen.

80
00:08:34,253 --> 00:08:36,598
The soldiers who play
with guns and cannons

81
00:08:37,542 --> 00:08:42,702
do not fear the police's
revolver, Mr. Dinesh.

82
00:08:48,739 --> 00:08:51,971
I came stealthily yet you found me out.

83
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:56,429
We soldiers have 4 not 2 eyes.

84
00:08:57,905 --> 00:09:00,303
- Oh brother, you...
- Hello.

85
00:09:00,342 --> 00:09:02,050
How come you came suddenly?

86
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,892
Mr. Dinesh Kapoor.
Sub-inspector of police.

87
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:08,997
I've come from Delhi to
give you some good news.

88
00:09:09,129 --> 00:09:10,947
- What is that?
- Not now.

89
00:09:11,524 --> 00:09:15,837
First some good piping hot
breakfast, then the news.

90
00:09:16,293 --> 00:09:19,053
- Done.
- The good news is I've been promoted.

91
00:09:19,490 --> 00:09:22,426
I have to join duty in
Bombay Within a week.

92
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:24,925
- Wow! Congratulations.
- Thank you.

93
00:09:24,949 --> 00:09:27,219
- Dinu. All the best.
- Thank you.

94
00:09:27,665 --> 00:09:32,067
And to celebrate we're going
to Simla by evening flight.

95
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,275
Here are the tickets.

96
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:37,051
Mr. Vijay Malhotra, Mrs. Geeta Malhotra

97
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:40,902
master Raju Malhotra
and Mr. Dinesh Kapoor.

98
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:41,910
Dinu.

99
00:09:42,793 --> 00:09:43,647
We won't be able to go.

100
00:09:43,878 --> 00:09:48,027
I'd promised Raju we'll go to a
hill station if he stands first.

101
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:50,592
Trucks with arms are going to the border.

102
00:09:51,365 --> 00:09:55,422
- I'm in charge of it.
- Hand it to somebody else.

103
00:09:55,593 --> 00:09:58,535
If it was given by an officer
I would have done this.

104
00:09:59,059 --> 00:10:03,061
But I've asked for this assignment.

105
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:06,867
You've ruined my plan.

106
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,208
Doesn't matter.
I'll go to Bombay today itself.

107
00:10:09,265 --> 00:10:10,425
Jaswant Dalal reporting sir.

108
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:13,385
- The jeep is ready sir.
- Wait for me.

109
00:10:38,735 --> 00:10:39,349
Stop the jeep.

110
00:10:43,072 --> 00:10:43,947
Driver, take it reverse.

111
00:10:47,373 --> 00:10:47,783
Sir.

112
00:10:49,512 --> 00:10:50,352
Why have you stopped the truck?

113
00:10:50,653 --> 00:10:52,964
There's an oil leak.
So the wheel is jammed.

114
00:11:03,581 --> 00:11:05,788
I'll try to contact headquarters.

115
00:11:14,438 --> 00:11:16,652
Hello. Hello.

116
00:11:17,313 --> 00:11:18,298
What's wrong with the wireless?

117
00:11:19,249 --> 00:11:21,096
- Listen.
- Sir.

118
00:11:21,844 --> 00:11:24,395
Some soldiers will remain
here with you for security.

119
00:11:24,459 --> 00:11:24,904
Sir.

120
00:11:25,595 --> 00:11:27,402
The rest will come with me.

121
00:11:27,919 --> 00:11:29,893
- I'll get help from the nearby station.
- Sir.

122
00:11:30,036 --> 00:11:31,236
- Any doubts?
- No, Sir.

123
00:12:14,357 --> 00:12:15,316
Back.

124
00:12:21,645 --> 00:12:22,357
Quickly.

125
00:12:22,899 --> 00:12:24,237
Pile it in.

126
00:12:57,553 --> 00:12:58,745
Bastards!

127
00:13:00,618 --> 00:13:04,191
These weapons are not bought from
the gold in a king's treasury!

128
00:13:06,561 --> 00:13:12,238
But by the sweat and
blood of 90 crore Indians!

129
00:13:13,348 --> 00:13:16,941
You swore to protect the
country but you loot it!

130
00:13:18,178 --> 00:13:22,123
It's a shame for this uniform
to be draped on your body!

131
00:13:22,459 --> 00:13:27,965
You'll get only some copper or
bronze medals by arresting us.

132
00:13:28,707 --> 00:13:32,271
Become our partner.
We'll give you one half!

133
00:13:35,476 --> 00:13:37,120
You want to buy me off!

134
00:13:37,866 --> 00:13:38,638
Bastard!

135
00:13:39,449 --> 00:13:43,754
Who are not on sale? Everybody is for sale.
At their own price.

136
00:13:44,361 --> 00:13:47,683
What will we soldiers do in this
environment by being honest?

137
00:13:47,723 --> 00:13:48,658
Silence!

138
00:13:49,101 --> 00:13:52,195
Our nation is safe because of our honesty!

139
00:13:52,595 --> 00:13:53,953
Or it would lose its' identity!

140
00:13:54,636 --> 00:13:57,223
People don't sleep because the sun sets.

141
00:13:58,038 --> 00:14:01,955
It's because we guard the border
when the country sleeps in peace!

142
00:14:02,181 --> 00:14:04,618
If we sell our honesty

143
00:14:05,309 --> 00:14:07,791
another color will fly
in place of our tricolor!

144
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:09,559
You are under arrest!

145
00:14:32,907 --> 00:14:34,213
Hey, get up.

146
00:16:51,591 --> 00:16:54,040
Sir, a fax from Interpol, Australia.

147
00:16:55,459 --> 00:16:57,515
Send a message to ACP Dinesh Kapoor.

148
00:16:57,739 --> 00:16:59,293
For an urgent meeting.

149
00:17:04,244 --> 00:17:05,764
- Good morning sir.
- Morning.

150
00:17:06,193 --> 00:17:07,362
Please sit down.

151
00:17:17,285 --> 00:17:18,523
Jaswant Dalal reporting sir.

152
00:17:19,656 --> 00:17:23,100
This is Jaswant Dalal.
We've got a message from Australia.

153
00:17:23,124 --> 00:17:25,911
He deals in illegal arms smuggling.

154
00:17:26,434 --> 00:17:29,301
He's coming to Bombay
by a cargo ship today.

155
00:17:30,074 --> 00:17:36,651
If we arrest him, we can find out
about illegal arms smuggling here.

156
00:17:38,061 --> 00:17:42,523
I've called for a secret meeting
so nobody outside hears about it.

157
00:17:43,078 --> 00:17:47,600
Otherwise people attached to
him, who'll suffer by his arrest

158
00:17:47,866 --> 00:17:48,823
will have to kill him.

159
00:17:51,238 --> 00:17:55,828
You'll be in charge of the
operation to nab Jaswant.

160
00:17:56,677 --> 00:18:00,988
And I want him alive
under any circumstance!

161
00:18:01,827 --> 00:18:02,466
Okay, sir.

162
00:18:47,173 --> 00:18:47,780
VICKY: Hello.

163
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:50,921
- Got the fax?
- VICKY: Yes.

164
00:18:51,955 --> 00:18:53,488
The police want him alive.

165
00:18:54,651 --> 00:18:56,428
You know what you have to do.

166
00:18:57,813 --> 00:19:02,134
Remember he must not get into
the police's hands alive.

167
00:19:02,788 --> 00:19:07,461
- DINESH: I cannot help you in this.
- VICKY: All right.

168
00:19:18,831 --> 00:19:20,053
- Is everything ready?
- Yes sir.

169
00:19:20,271 --> 00:19:21,342
He can't escape.

170
00:19:21,427 --> 00:19:23,533
There are more policemen
than workers here.

171
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:34,352
Sir.

172
00:19:37,466 --> 00:19:39,554
Jaswant has come.
Shall we begin the movement?

173
00:19:42,298 --> 00:19:42,914
Yes!

174
00:20:02,633 --> 00:20:04,395
Who are you? What do you want?

175
00:20:04,889 --> 00:20:07,845
- To save your life.
- Whom do I fear?

176
00:20:08,853 --> 00:20:10,445
Whom every criminal fears.

177
00:20:11,111 --> 00:20:13,544
The ones outside are
the police not workers.

178
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,315
Police?

179
00:20:18,075 --> 00:20:21,559
The police can be recognized
by their shoes not clothes.

180
00:20:26,653 --> 00:20:28,413
If you want to get out of here

181
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,199
do as I say.

182
00:20:31,573 --> 00:20:32,124
Okay.

183
00:20:37,295 --> 00:20:39,440
Sir. Jaswant is not to be seen.

184
00:20:45,247 --> 00:20:46,327
Nobody here.

185
00:21:02,893 --> 00:21:03,454
Hello!

186
00:21:04,758 --> 00:21:07,241
Jaswant is in the container
that is being off loaded!

187
00:21:07,778 --> 00:21:09,198
There's another man with him!

188
00:21:11,294 --> 00:21:13,111
Should we surround the container?

189
00:21:14,014 --> 00:21:15,495
- Hello!
- Hello!

190
00:21:16,311 --> 00:21:18,018
- Yes.
- All units alert!

191
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:20,658
Surround the container being off loaded.

192
00:21:29,996 --> 00:21:32,801
- Stop the container!
- Stop the container!

193
00:21:42,773 --> 00:21:43,693
Bring the container down.

194
00:21:46,973 --> 00:21:49,710
Nobody will fire. We want him alive.

195
00:22:45,616 --> 00:22:46,051
Good.

196
00:23:10,644 --> 00:23:12,779
So far I did what you said.

197
00:23:14,506 --> 00:23:16,119
Now you'll do what I say.

198
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:17,019
Stop the car.

199
00:23:21,235 --> 00:23:21,683
Stop.

200
00:23:29,773 --> 00:23:30,146
Out.

201
00:23:31,584 --> 00:23:32,296
Come on.

202
00:23:40,203 --> 00:23:43,011
Hands up.

203
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:45,632
Move.

204
00:23:52,192 --> 00:23:52,810
Good.

205
00:23:53,659 --> 00:23:56,274
You're very useful man but my principle is

206
00:23:57,323 --> 00:23:59,521
job finished, man finished.

207
00:24:22,621 --> 00:24:26,821
And my principle is man
finished, job finished.

208
00:24:28,053 --> 00:24:29,773
I want the killer not your sorry!

209
00:24:30,813 --> 00:24:33,924
Seal all the ways of going out.

210
00:24:35,031 --> 00:24:39,069
And remember he should not
leave the city! Got it!

211
00:25:02,007 --> 00:25:03,709
- One Minta Car Road please.
- Yes.

212
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:09,624
- Are you an Indian?
- You recognised me?

213
00:25:10,536 --> 00:25:11,660
- No.
- No?

214
00:25:14,354 --> 00:25:15,794
- Now?
- No.

215
00:25:18,029 --> 00:25:21,634
No, I didn't recognize you.

216
00:25:30,822 --> 00:25:34,422
- Why you started crying?
- It's a sad story.

217
00:25:34,963 --> 00:25:37,279
Once there was a fair of Kumbh.

218
00:25:37,334 --> 00:25:39,342
- In Australia?
- No, India.

219
00:25:39,648 --> 00:25:42,484
I have a twin brother named Sohan.
I'm Mohan.

220
00:25:43,227 --> 00:25:45,108
He was left and I right

221
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,658
- and in the center was...
- Your mom.

222
00:25:46,782 --> 00:25:51,512
My dad. We were happily
going when all of a sudden

223
00:25:51,536 --> 00:25:53,397
- he ran away with my bag.
- Who, your Dad?

224
00:25:53,563 --> 00:25:54,845
No, a thief.

225
00:25:55,523 --> 00:25:56,540
I am helpless.

226
00:25:56,637 --> 00:25:59,210
I screamed, Dad!
He's running away with the bag!

227
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:01,069
- He ran after him.
- Who, your Dad?

228
00:26:01,222 --> 00:26:03,901
My brother was behind the thief.

229
00:26:04,114 --> 00:26:08,495
They were running and I screamed
and he fell with a thud!

230
00:26:08,543 --> 00:26:09,829
- Your brother?
- My Dad!

231
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,952
He was drunk and the police caught him.

232
00:26:14,074 --> 00:26:15,717
- The thief?
- My Dad!

233
00:26:16,198 --> 00:26:18,642
- And started beating him.
- But why?

234
00:26:18,747 --> 00:26:21,717
They thought he was the thief.
In the meantime he ran away!

235
00:26:21,867 --> 00:26:23,264
- The thief?
- My brother!

236
00:26:24,245 --> 00:26:25,872
Since then I'm looking for him.

237
00:26:26,017 --> 00:26:27,829
- The thief?
- No! My brother!

238
00:26:28,130 --> 00:26:30,656
But if he was lost in India why
are you looking for him here?

239
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:34,370
That was different. He ran away.

240
00:26:34,850 --> 00:26:40,145
He had two hobbies,
to see kangaroos and pick pockets.

241
00:26:40,617 --> 00:26:43,474
Tell me, is any place better
than trams to pick pockets?

242
00:26:43,692 --> 00:26:45,695
That's why I took this job.

243
00:26:46,415 --> 00:26:50,164
I thought someday he'll come here
to pick pocket and I'll see him.

244
00:26:50,457 --> 00:26:52,092
And I'll meet him. It's come!

245
00:26:52,602 --> 00:26:54,372
- Your brother?
- No, your station!

246
00:26:54,890 --> 00:26:55,572
Oh!

247
00:26:59,203 --> 00:27:00,548
Listen! Listen! Listen!

248
00:27:00,690 --> 00:27:04,175
If you ever see that
rascal whom I'm looking for

249
00:27:04,277 --> 00:27:07,340
- give him my card.
- Whom? The thief?

250
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:10,034
To my brother, Sohan!

251
00:27:10,567 --> 00:27:12,559
Turned my head round!

252
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:14,373
