01:12:02,738 --> 01:12:04,859
We will kill DK and 2 will remain.

768
01:12:05,594 --> 01:12:08,280
You kill me and only you are left.

769
01:12:09,389 --> 01:12:11,969
Do you think I'm a village idiot?

770
01:12:12,487 --> 01:12:14,760
You want to grab the entire organization?

771
01:12:15,220 --> 01:12:18,494
I find your intentions
dishonorable not DK's.

772
01:12:18,562 --> 01:12:22,245
- Shut up or...!
- Control yourself.

773
01:12:22,785 --> 01:12:25,800
You'll be finding your fingers
if they touch the trigger.

774
01:12:26,130 --> 01:12:31,125
I'm not Jaswant.
Firstly I won't die so easily.

775
01:12:31,943 --> 01:12:36,869
Even if I die, I won't become
a police file or news in paper.

776
01:12:37,477 --> 01:12:42,202
If you have a file on me,
I have a file of your deeds.

777
01:12:42,891 --> 01:12:45,031
That file will go to the
police as soon as I die.

778
01:12:50,002 --> 01:12:53,557
What's the matter?
Changed your tune by seeing the gun?

779
01:12:54,405 --> 01:12:55,709
Laughing instead of crying.

780
01:12:58,193 --> 01:13:03,217
Hats off to you friend!
I was talking about killing DK

781
01:13:03,532 --> 01:13:08,819
because I wanted to know if you
had a hand in killing Jaswant.

782
01:13:09,783 --> 01:13:11,811
If you were responsible

783
01:13:12,360 --> 01:13:15,205
you would agree with me.

784
01:13:16,005 --> 01:13:18,544
So what have you decided?

785
01:13:19,698 --> 01:13:22,259
That you haven't changed.

786
01:13:22,895 --> 01:13:25,454
You're still a friend of friends.
As you were 20 years ago.

787
01:13:26,025 --> 01:13:28,327
Nobody can divide us 3 partners.

788
01:13:29,114 --> 01:13:30,341
Except for death!

789
01:13:31,372 --> 01:13:33,405
Yes. Except for death!

790
01:13:35,505 --> 01:13:39,007
Do you see that island?
Dad bought it for my last birthday.

791
01:13:39,686 --> 01:13:42,817
And that island?
That was on my first birthday.

792
01:13:42,861 --> 01:13:43,582
Really?

793
01:13:43,965 --> 01:13:47,024
So your dad buys you a new
island for every birthday?

794
01:13:47,212 --> 01:13:48,882
Yes, and that to in my name.

795
01:13:49,125 --> 01:13:50,974
Don't tell this to anybody else.

796
01:13:51,645 --> 01:13:54,104
- Why?
- It will let out your age.

797
01:13:54,517 --> 01:13:55,312
You!

798
01:13:59,625 --> 01:14:02,594
Look there. That's my dad.

799
01:14:06,446 --> 01:14:07,178
Hi.

800
01:14:11,775 --> 01:14:14,325
- Come my darling come, come, come.
- Hi Dad.

801
01:14:15,534 --> 01:14:16,597
- This is...
- Vicky.

802
01:14:17,272 --> 01:14:17,827
Wow!

803
01:14:18,389 --> 01:14:20,400
You know his name without telling you?

804
01:14:20,612 --> 01:14:23,207
When he knows the color of
my clothes from miles away

805
01:14:24,291 --> 01:14:27,221
- he can know my name too.
- While giving a daughter

806
01:14:27,532 --> 01:14:29,992
work is seen in addition to name.

807
01:14:30,495 --> 01:14:33,360
- Whatever he does, is great!
- Really?

808
01:14:33,717 --> 01:14:38,872
We'll see. You go in,
we have to talk about business.

809
01:14:40,001 --> 01:14:40,499
Okay.

810
01:14:47,932 --> 01:14:48,847
Tell me, Vicky.

811
01:14:49,991 --> 01:14:55,180
First tell me who gave you
the contract to kill Jaswant?

812
01:14:56,429 --> 01:14:58,483
So you know about my work?

813
01:14:59,872 --> 01:15:03,427
Anyway hear my principles too.

814
01:15:04,177 --> 01:15:07,664
I see the cash while accepting a
contract, not the payer.

815
01:15:07,792 --> 01:15:13,807
You haven't seen the man who gave
you a contract to love my daughter?

816
01:15:13,942 --> 01:15:19,994
Pratap Sir! I accept contracts for
killing not to play game of love!

817
01:15:20,722 --> 01:15:22,654
Preeti's love and mine is not a game.

818
01:15:22,908 --> 01:15:27,840
Maybe but a dad won't
give his daughter to a man

819
01:15:28,342 --> 01:15:29,857
whose hands are tainted with blood.

820
01:15:30,501 --> 01:15:33,690
If mine are tainted,
are yours milky white?

821
01:15:35,246 --> 01:15:37,086
Even I know about you.

822
01:15:37,792 --> 01:15:39,652
We belong to the same community.

823
01:15:41,354 --> 01:15:43,462
Community but not position.

824
01:15:44,437 --> 01:15:48,584
You are a paid ass in this
business Whereas I'm a lion!

825
01:15:49,477 --> 01:15:51,750
You've reached here because
you came with my child.

826
01:15:52,491 --> 01:15:57,000
Otherwise my security dogs wouldn't
have let your bones come near me.

827
01:15:58,860 --> 01:16:01,762
For the first time,
I've seen dogs guarding a lion!

828
01:16:03,623 --> 01:16:04,777
Just Listen to 2 things
that I have to say.

829
01:16:05,555 --> 01:16:09,089
In today's world,
lions can be safe in only 2 places.

830
01:16:09,578 --> 01:16:12,171
In the circus and in the zoo!

831
01:16:13,574 --> 01:16:15,609
Secondly, regarding position.

832
01:16:16,704 --> 01:16:21,014
I can take you to that place

833
01:16:21,600 --> 01:16:23,770
that you're dreaming of for 20 years.

834
01:16:24,458 --> 01:16:26,354
But can never reach it.

835
01:16:28,544 --> 01:16:29,085
Means?

836
01:17:09,319 --> 01:17:09,829
Hello.

837
01:17:10,296 --> 01:17:15,123
Saw what I broke in place
of two teeth of mine?

838
01:17:17,937 --> 01:17:19,301
Pomeranian Puppy!

839
01:17:20,629 --> 01:17:22,358
Give the line to your Pop, the bulldog.

840
01:17:23,047 --> 01:17:23,641
Dad.

841
01:17:23,921 --> 01:17:26,136
- What is it?
- He called me a puppy!

842
01:17:26,536 --> 01:17:27,417
And me?

843
01:17:28,234 --> 01:17:28,973
Bulldog.

844
01:17:29,217 --> 01:17:31,594
He called me a bulldog? Give me the phone!

845
01:17:32,306 --> 01:17:34,339
Are we a family of dogs?

846
01:17:34,754 --> 01:17:38,472
I didn't find you or
I'd have broken you too!

847
01:17:38,712 --> 01:17:41,246
You won't believe, I'm very bad!

848
01:17:41,482 --> 01:17:43,909
When you will meet me,
You will become nervous.

849
01:17:44,074 --> 01:17:46,077
We're a family of tigers not dogs!

850
01:17:46,257 --> 01:17:48,672
We bite not bark!

851
01:17:48,784 --> 01:17:50,344
We eat raw people!

852
01:17:50,495 --> 01:17:51,611
Are you frightened?

853
01:17:51,942 --> 01:17:53,584
Why aren't you speaking? Hello?

854
01:17:53,660 --> 01:17:55,125
Can you hear?

855
01:17:55,253 --> 01:17:58,201
I'm talking to you not myself!

856
01:17:59,195 --> 01:18:04,549
I've been yelling for ages! I'm not mad!

857
01:18:04,984 --> 01:18:06,289
Total 8500.

858
01:18:06,574 --> 01:18:08,869
- Plus 100% tax.
- What?

859
01:18:11,801 --> 01:18:15,312
Total 17000. Round figure 20000.

860
01:18:15,634 --> 01:18:18,086
Which figure are you
rounding and squaring?

861
01:18:18,326 --> 01:18:21,672
This is the damage your
son did to my house.

862
01:18:21,807 --> 01:18:24,611
- You'll take money from me?
- Not rupees, in dollars.

863
01:18:25,447 --> 01:18:29,786
My bill will reach you at 3.55

864
01:18:30,582 --> 01:18:32,285
I'll come at 4 to take the cash.

865
01:18:32,814 --> 01:18:34,866
And leave at 4.05.

866
01:18:36,303 --> 01:18:38,978
10 minutes for giving and taking.

867
01:18:39,913 --> 01:18:43,122
Take those 10 minutes seriously. Got it?

868
01:18:45,117 --> 01:18:47,637
- What happened?
- Nothing, he talks rot!

869
01:18:47,967 --> 01:18:50,179
Says he'll send the bill at 3.55

870
01:18:50,426 --> 01:18:53,989
and will leave at 4:05.
As if we're here to pay cash!

871
01:18:54,109 --> 01:18:55,032
Are we donkeys?

872
01:18:55,992 --> 01:19:00,266
The arms buyers would have come,
bring them in. Let me do some work.

873
01:19:02,403 --> 01:19:03,131
Gentlemen.

874
01:19:03,724 --> 01:19:05,038
We have machine guns.

875
01:19:05,284 --> 01:19:09,566
Mouser.. AK-47, AK-56, AK-98

876
01:19:09,949 --> 01:19:14,584
even those not yet in the market.
We have 2 lakh pieces of each.

877
01:19:14,906 --> 01:19:16,901
We'll send you the guns you need.

878
01:19:18,224 --> 01:19:18,723
Next.

879
01:19:20,110 --> 01:19:22,879
This is a pipe gun.

880
01:19:23,164 --> 01:19:24,385
This pipe gun blast people.

881
01:19:24,626 --> 01:19:28,564
With every pipe gun,
you get a dozen Hamam soaps free.

882
01:19:29,014 --> 01:19:30,109
Oh Hamam?

883
01:19:30,500 --> 01:19:32,336
Now show them our bomb section.

884
01:19:40,876 --> 01:19:42,766
Wow! Good idea to display bomb.

885
01:19:42,901 --> 01:19:44,588
You have displayed bomb nicely.

886
01:19:44,763 --> 01:19:45,256
Thank you.

887
01:19:47,813 --> 01:19:48,848
- Dad.
- Yes.

888
01:19:49,101 --> 01:19:50,599
- 3:55.
- 3:55?

889
01:19:53,835 --> 01:19:55,830
This is real bomb.

890
01:19:55,854 --> 01:19:58,186
- Run.
- Run.

891
01:20:15,999 --> 01:20:18,046
Dad! It's the phone ringing dad.

892
01:20:22,202 --> 01:20:22,755
Hello.

893
01:20:27,270 --> 01:20:30,399
Don't be scared. It's the bill not a bomb.

894
01:20:35,596 --> 01:20:38,004
What do you think? I got scared?

895
01:20:38,498 --> 01:20:40,750
I play with such bombs day and night.

896
01:20:40,996 --> 01:20:43,344
I deal with them. Where are you?

897
01:20:46,691 --> 01:20:48,750
- John!
- John!

898
01:20:49,230 --> 01:20:51,084
- What happened dad?
- He's come downstairs.

899
01:20:52,719 --> 01:20:55,118
Tell him I'm taking the lift up.

900
01:20:55,659 --> 01:20:56,776
He is coming by lift.

901
01:20:57,074 --> 01:20:58,250
- What?
- Yes sir.

902
01:21:26,015 --> 01:21:28,211
Stop! Stop firing! Stop firing!

903
01:21:30,618 --> 01:21:31,033
John!

904
01:21:56,962 --> 01:21:58,904
Dad! Dad!

905
01:23:16,088 --> 01:23:17,898
Well done.

906
01:23:19,146 --> 01:23:20,422
You did very well!

907
01:23:21,419 --> 01:23:23,091
I thought you were good for nothing.

908
01:23:23,640 --> 01:23:26,324
But you proved to be very smart!

909
01:23:27,413 --> 01:23:30,187
You deserve all the praise!

910
01:23:31,589 --> 01:23:34,259
And you called me a bulldog!

911
01:23:35,497 --> 01:23:39,284
Whether a dog bites or
licks, both are dangerous!

912
01:23:44,114 --> 01:23:45,299
His pistol is empty.

913
01:23:56,595 --> 01:23:57,690
Dad!

914
01:23:59,090 --> 01:24:02,189
Don't move or else the bullet
will go off in your ear.

915
01:24:02,543 --> 01:24:04,237
But it will bleed from some other place.

916
01:24:05,366 --> 01:24:05,917
Cash.

917
01:24:38,708 --> 01:24:40,170
Sir nobody is here.

918
01:24:45,727 --> 01:24:48,434
Pomeranian puppy!

919
01:25:01,081 --> 01:25:03,547
No, no, no. You please send
money within half an hour.

920
01:25:04,590 --> 01:25:06,344
Baldev! It's a very big deal.

921
01:25:06,525 --> 01:25:08,208
- Call George.
- He's in hospital.

922
01:25:08,247 --> 01:25:11,512
- Then call Kalia or Rahim.
- They both are also in the hospital.

923
01:25:11,633 --> 01:25:13,874
Is the gorilla also in the hospital?

924
01:25:13,951 --> 01:25:15,704
Unfortunately he is also in the hospital.

925
01:25:16,441 --> 01:25:17,619
What they are doing in the hospital?

926
01:25:17,756 --> 01:25:19,650
Have they gone to get a corpse
or have they all got aids?

927
01:25:19,802 --> 01:25:22,823
You know uncle.
This is all because of that Indian.

928
01:25:23,265 --> 01:25:26,205
First he burnt my teeth
then he bashed up my men.

929
01:25:26,504 --> 01:25:29,280
And on top of that he called
me a Pomeranian puppy and him.

930
01:25:29,601 --> 01:25:30,255
Bull dog.

931
01:25:30,923 --> 01:25:32,699
Then he did a miracle!

932
01:25:32,723 --> 01:25:35,189
- What?
- He thrashed Dad.

933
01:25:35,504 --> 01:25:38,337
He took money from him for all
the damage I did to his house.

934
01:25:40,372 --> 01:25:46,245
Rascal! Recounting the tale of his
bashing as if he's won a medal!

935
01:25:46,508 --> 01:25:48,404
He's not an ordinary boy.

936
01:25:48,428 --> 01:25:52,867
Then is he a King Kong?
If the tale of my shame spreads

937
01:25:53,130 --> 01:25:54,892
I won't have the face to return to Patna!

938
01:25:55,388 --> 01:25:57,322
Go and take my marksman with you.

939
01:25:57,545 --> 01:25:59,234
What do we say.. Yes, sharp shooter.

940
01:25:59,548 --> 01:26:04,837
Go, shoot him! If you come without
shooting him, I'll shoot all of you!

941
01:26:38,196 --> 01:26:39,824
The rascal's mother is coming.

942
01:26:41,701 --> 01:26:44,529
He will go to the airport to receive her.

943
01:27:18,178 --> 01:27:19,147
I'll kill him.

944
01:27:19,356 --> 01:27:21,189
- Give me the gun.
- Okay.

945
01:27:28,131 --> 01:27:29,063
Jojo Shoot.

946
01:27:33,585 --> 01:27:34,327
Shoot him Jojo!

947
01:27:38,054 --> 01:27:39,157
He went behind.

948
01:27:40,836 --> 01:27:41,527
Now!

949
01:27:46,883 --> 01:27:48,735
- Shit!
- Where's that rascal come from?

950
01:27:51,588 --> 01:27:53,514
- Mother has come.
- Now kill him Jojo!

951
01:27:57,591 --> 01:27:58,477
Shoot Jojo!

952
01:28:05,129 --> 01:28:06,104
Sister-in-law?

953
01:28:08,908 --> 01:28:10,544
- Stop!
- What's wrong?

954
01:28:10,905 --> 01:28:12,780
This is my sister-in-law!

955
01:28:14,030 --> 01:28:18,765
That means this is my elder brother's son!

956
01:28:19,327 --> 01:28:21,149
This is our own blood!

957
01:28:21,855 --> 01:28:26,640
If brother hears this good news,
he will give all his property of Patna.

958
01:28:42,487 --> 01:28:44,663
Uncle will be happy to hear it!

959
01:28:48,335 --> 01:28:48,974
Shanti.

960
01:28:50,063 --> 01:28:51,814
- In Australia?
- Yes!

961
01:28:51,975 --> 01:28:53,092
I am telling the truth.

962
01:28:53,258 --> 01:28:57,412
The boy we went to kill is
actually your son Vicky!

963
01:28:57,691 --> 01:29:00,187
My son! My Shanti!

964
01:29:01,260 --> 01:29:04,245
I can't believe it Baldev!
Are you telling the truth?

965
01:29:04,269 --> 01:29:07,020
Yes. Brother,
Jojo you tell him what you have seen.

966
01:29:07,129 --> 01:29:11,992
Dad is right. We ourselves saw
brother Vicky touching her feet.

967
01:29:14,684 --> 01:29:17,663
My son! Shanti!

968
01:29:21,563 --> 01:29:22,844
You've come to the wrong address.

969
01:29:23,777 --> 01:29:26,775
Vicky's mother stays here not your wife.

970
01:29:27,082 --> 01:29:31,597
Think why fate has brought us
together in a foreign land?

971
01:29:32,391 --> 01:29:33,973
Just, so that we can live together.

972
01:29:34,883 --> 01:29:38,227
A child who pretends to be
an orphan will get his dad.

973
01:29:38,820 --> 01:29:42,855
Orphans are those kids who
have neither dad nor mother.

974
01:29:44,535 --> 01:29:46,229
And Vicky's mother is alive.

975
01:29:46,408 --> 01:29:52,012
Don't be adamant. Today I have so
much wealth I can buy anything.

976
01:29:52,523 --> 01:29:56,092
Then go and buy yourself a wife and a son.

977
01:29:57,450 --> 01:30:01,132
People who sell themselves for
money don't live in this house.

978
01:30:01,567 --> 01:30:05,775
Please forget everything.
I apologize on brother's behalf.

979
01:30:08,108 --> 01:30:11,069
The man who sells his motherland

980
01:30:12,030 --> 01:30:14,100
who is responsible for
the death of innocents

981
01:30:15,135 --> 01:30:18,375
they deserve punishment not forgiveness.

982
01:30:19,927 --> 01:30:21,052
You all may leave.

983
01:30:21,645 --> 01:30:22,192
Shanti.

984
01:30:22,984 --> 01:30:24,546
Shanti, Listen to me.

985
01:30:26,917 --> 01:30:29,587
Brother, this is your son!

986
01:30:33,394 --> 01:30:34,207
Vicky.

987
01:30:37,995 --> 01:30:41,152
- Son, You don't know me, son...
- I know.

988
01:30:42,518 --> 01:30:43,632
I have heard everything.

989
01:30:44,512 --> 01:30:48,674
Son! My son!

990
01:30:49,238 --> 01:30:50,710
Don't be angry with me.

991
01:30:51,787 --> 01:30:53,867
I'm pining for you since 20 years!

992
01:30:54,428 --> 01:30:57,450
Even I've been pining
for my dad for 20 years!

993
01:30:59,078 --> 01:31:01,807
Blood is thicker than water.

994
01:31:02,167 --> 01:31:05,164
Yes, uncle. Blood is after all blood.

995
01:31:06,233 --> 01:31:11,010
- Now if Shanti agrees...
- Leave her to me.

996
01:31:11,551 --> 01:31:12,434
I'll convince her.

997
01:31:13,382 --> 01:31:17,189
Organize a great party now!

998
01:31:17,805 --> 01:31:21,480
I'll announce to the world
that I'm not childless!

999
01:31:22,780 --> 01:31:26,280
His son who will work with him
shoulder to shoulder has come!

1000
01:31:28,830 --> 01:31:31,374
Welcome, welcome. This is my son Vicky.

1001
01:31:31,553 --> 01:31:32,459
- Mr. Marshall.
- Hello.

1002
01:31:32,503 --> 01:31:33,968
Please sit down. Enjoy yourself.

1003
01:31:35,037 --> 01:31:38,430
Singhania sir, Come. Come.

1004
01:31:52,485 --> 01:31:54,050
- You?
- Yes me?

1005
01:31:54,375 --> 01:31:55,792
- You have a brother?
- Yes.

1006
01:31:56,158 --> 01:31:57,211
- Twin brother?
- Yes.

1007
01:31:57,532 --> 01:31:59,212
- Who was lost in the kumbh fair?
- Yes.

1008
01:31:59,378 --> 01:32:02,729
- He's come to look for you from India!
- Where is he?

1009
01:32:02,753 --> 01:32:06,086
- He becomes a policeman, waiter...
- And sometimes band master!

1010
01:32:06,313 --> 01:32:08,318
You always find me only!

1011
01:32:09,390 --> 01:32:10,837
I'm Mohan!

1012
01:32:11,704 --> 01:32:14,616
I thought my brother would
have become a smuggler.

1013
01:32:14,940 --> 01:32:17,077
They keep doing parties here.

1014
01:32:17,505 --> 01:32:19,800
Someday I'll find him singing and dancing.

1015
01:32:20,138 --> 01:32:23,685
Lord! Why did you make kumbh fair?

1016
01:32:23,714 --> 01:32:25,514
- Hey play man!
- Yeah.

1017
01:32:28,374 --> 01:32:29,295
Enjoy yourself.

